{
  "card_id": "htf_ltf_analysis",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "HTF-LTF Analysis",
  "aliases": [
    "High Time Frame-Low Time Frame Analysis",
    "high time frame-low time frame analysis",
    "HTF/LTF Pairing",
    "Multi-timeframe Analysis",
    "Time Frame Alignment",
    "time frame pairing",
    "Time Frame Pairing"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "Multi-timeframe analysis that confirms higher time frame bias (e.g., daily candle 2 closure, sweep, expansion) with intermediate time frame structural confirmation (change in state of delivery) and lower time frame entry trigger (e.g., continuation order block, inversion) before executing a trade. Uses fractal pairs (e.g., daily–hourly–5m) to align bias, structure, and entry.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Establish HTF directional bias by identifying a candle 2 closure (sweep of prior candle’s high or low followed by close back inside its range) at a point of interest, or by confirming expansion characteristics (small opposing wick, large body in intended direction); define draw on liquidity (e.g., previous day/weekly high/low).",
    "Confirm HTF candle effective closure (candle 2 or 3 close through key level); invalid closure stops analysis.",
    "Drop to intermediate time frame (fractal level below HTF, e.g., hourly from daily, 15m from 4h) and confirm a change in state of delivery (CISD): close through the series of opposing candles that formed the HTF sweep, or a candle 2/3 closure in same direction, establishing a valid swing point.",
    "Drop to lower entry time frame (level below ITF, e.g., 5m from hourly, 1m from 5m) and wait for a continuation entry pattern (order block, fair value gap inversion, or continuation OB) formed in same direction, ideally inside HTF candle’s wick/body or anticipated t-spot.",
    "Confirm all utilized time frames (minimum two, typically three) point in same direction; if any disagrees, trade is invalid.",
    "Use established fractal time frame pairs: common pairings are weekly–daily–hourly, daily–hourly–5m/15m, 4h–15m, 30m–3m, monthly–weekly–4h. Do not anchor HTF analysis below 4-hour chart.",
    "HTF candle must have small opposing wick on entry side; large opposing wick or run is reversal candle and invalidates alignment. If HTF candle 2 closure appears weak (resembling expansion candle in opposite direction), demand stronger LTF confirmation.",
    "In OTE-based variant, after HTF displacement, draw Fibonacci retracement (0.5–0.79 zone) and require ITF to retrace into that zone (ideally filling an FVG); LTF entry must occur within that HTF OTE/POI during a kill zone.",
    "In hourly–5m–1m fractal model, after hourly sweep and 5m CISD, mark t-spot (zone of expected HTF wick) and enter only on 1-minute inversion (close through FVG) within that t-spot.",
    "When daily paired with hourly, reject setups where hourly candle closes beyond prior day’s equilibrium (EQ) against bias. For bullish intraday bias, price should open, form low, then close above hourly CISD level.",
    "Simplest alignment is candle 3 (continuation candle) occurring simultaneously on multiple time frames. If current HTF candle is reversal candle, defer entries until next candle opens."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Time frame pairing filters entries to moments when HTF bias, ITF structural confirmation, and LTF entry trigger all agree, increasing probability of sustained expansion toward HTF liquidity targets (previous day high/low, failure swings). Enter on continuation patterns (order blocks, fair value gaps) with stops on protected swings, aiming for at least 2R. Misalignment (missing CISD, weak candle 2 closure, reversal HTF candle) signals waiting. Without HTF support, targets must be conservative (e.g., daily open).",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Trading lower time frame setups without first establishing a higher time frame bias (pattern-trading in isolation).",
    "Entering before the required change in state of delivery (CISD) has occurred on the appropriate time frame.",
    "Accepting a weak candle 2 closure (resembling expansion candle in opposite direction) without demanding stronger lower time frame confirmation.",
    "Calling a CISD before price has actually closed through the opposing series of candles.",
    "Using time frame pairs anchored below the 4-hour chart, degrading structure clarity.",
    "Accepting lower time frame closes beyond the daily equilibrium (EQ) opposite the bias and still expecting the HTF scenario to play out.",
    "Forcing an entry when no valid inversion, continuation order block, or PD array appears in the designated entry zone (t-spot, OTE area).",
    "Taking an OTE-based entry when the retracement zone is reached outside a kill zone.",
    "Ignoring nested PD arrays (FVG, breaker, order block) inside the LTF OTE that provide the actual trigger.",
    "Using mismatched time frame pairs (e.g., 5-minute off a 30-minute swing instead of 30m–3m).",
    "Refining down to a lower time frame when the intermediate structural time frame already offers a valid entry trigger at a point of interest.",
    "Trading in the opposite direction after a failed candle 2 closure instead of waiting for a new aligned swing point.",
    "Entering when any one of the aligned time frames disagrees with the others, expecting expansion.",
    "Placing limit orders at points of interest without waiting for price reaction, risking unnecessary losses.",
    "Expecting a full expansion move when the higher time frame candle is a reversal candle, instead of reducing targets to intraday levels.",
    "Trying to pick a bottom/top on a current reversal HTF candle instead of deferring to the next candle when alignment improves.",
    "Ignoring the size of the HTF candle’s opposing wick; a large wick invalidates expansion potential.",
    "Forcing trades in a grinding environment where price never sweeps a swing or reaches a fair value gap, preventing proper alignment.",
    "Not verifying that the intraday OHLC aligns with the bias in the daily–hourly pair (e.g., for a bullish bias, price must open, form a low, and close above the hourly CISD).",
    "Viewing a lower time frame model on a chart time frame higher than the model’s intended lower bound (indicator error).",
    "Only relying on HTF candle patterns or closure without waiting for LTF CSD confirmation, leading to entries at false breakouts.",
    "Analyzing LTF when HTF closure is invalid, wasting time.",
    "Trading immediately when price approaches HTF key level on LTF without confirming CSD.",
    "Confusing CSD definition: CSD requires finding the candle series forming the high/low and confirming close through that level, not just price touching the level.",
    "Confusing wick size meaning: large wick requires waiting for candle three or subsequent candles for continuation; small wick supports immediate reversal trade.",
    "Finding good LTF patterns but ignoring HTF trend direction, leading to counter-trend trades.",
    "Forcing setups when HTF trend is unclear, increasing false signal risk.",
    "Over-relying on LTF while ignoring HTF support/resistance, causing stops to be swept."
  ],
